With an unmanned, half-mile-long freight train barreling toward a city, a veteran engineer and a young conductor race against the clock to prevent a catastrophe.

A young man from the countryside uses his skills in silat martial arts to survive the slave trade.

A Texas teenager cuts her hair short and becomes an outlaw martyr with her brother and friends.

Truckers form a mile-long "convoy" in support of a trucker's vendetta with an abusive sheriff - Based on the country song of the same title by C.W. McCall.

Rescued as a child by the legendary assassin Moody, Anna is the world's most skilled contract killer. However, when Moody is brutally killed, she vows revenge for the man who taught her everything she knows.
A mysterious stranger and a random act of violence drag a town of misfits and nitwits into the bloody crosshairs of revenge.
A nameless gunfighter arrives in a town ripped apart by rival gangs and, though courted by both to join, chooses his own path.
Two U.S. Marines in World War II are assigned to protect Navajo Marines, who use their native language as an unbreakable radio cypher.
A young martial artist's unparalleled Tai Chi skills land him in a highly lucrative underworld fight club.
Revolves around Frank, an American tourist visiting Italy to mend a broken heart. Elise is an extraordinary woman who deliberately crosses his path.
A woman asks her ex-lover for help in order to save her outlaw husband from a gang out to kill him.

5 Southern friends return home when the war ends 1865. But Yankee soldiers and Pinkerton are busy helping a railroad baron grab land from farmers along the planned railroad west. The 5 friends fight back.

Three soldiers struggle to readjust to life at home after returning home from a lengthy tour in Iraq.
The film covers through fiction real-life events like the occupation of Iraq, the execution of Daniel Pearl, the Hood event and the Abu Ghraib torture scandal.

A woman fights to protect her family during a home invasion.

A one-man army comes to the rescue of the United States when a spy attempts an invasion.

A son of the leader of a legendary group of an urban biker gang tries to retain his championship title.
A young hot shot driver is in the middle of a championship season and is coming apart at the seams. A former CART champion is called in to give him guidance.
When a devastating illness threatens to end Evan Lake's career in the C.I.A., he goes rogue to hunt down a terrorist who tortured him during a mission gone awry years ago.
Archaeology professor Indiana Jones ventures to seize a biblical artefact known as the Ark of the Covenant. While doing so, he puts up a fight against Renee and a troop of Nazis.

column1: Indiana Jones et la derniere croisade
column8: In 1938, after his father Professor Henry Jones, Sr. goes missing while pursuing the Holy Grail, Professor Henry "Indiana" Jones, Jr. finds himself up against Adolf Hitler's Nazis again to stop them from obtaining its powers.

column1: Stand by Me : Compte sur moi
column8: After the death of one of his friends, a writer recounts a childhood journey with his friends to find the body of a missing boy.
After a Jewish prince is betrayed and sent into slavery by a Roman friend in 1st-century Jerusalem, he regains his freedom and comes back for revenge.
The story of Brian Sweeney Fitzgerald, an extremely determined man who intends to build an opera house in the middle of a jungle.
James Bond's loyalty to M is tested when her past comes back to haunt her. When MI6 comes under attack, 007 must track down and destroy the threat, no matter how personal the cost.

The Dark Knight of Gotham City begins his war on crime with his first major enemy being Jack Napier, a criminal who becomes the clownishly homicidal Joker.

column1: Indiana Jones et le Temple maudit

Ethan and his team take on their most impossible mission yet when they have to eradicate an international rogue organization as highly skilled as they are and committed to destroying the IMF.

Set in 1825, Clare, a young Irish convict woman, chases a British officer through the rugged Tasmanian wilderness, bent on revenge for a terrible act of violence he committed against her family. On the way she enlists the services of an Aboriginal tracker named Billy, who is also marked by trauma from his own violence-filled past.
Two bikers head from L.A. to New Orleans through the open country and desert lands, and along the way they meet a man who bridges a counter-culture gap of which they had been unaware.
An arrogant Texas millionaire hires four adventurers to rescue his kidnapped wife from a notorious Mexican bandit.
The sole survivor of a lost whaling ship relates the tale of his captain's self-destructive obsession to hunt the white whale, Moby Dick.
A father and his thirteen-year-old daughter are living an ideal existence in a vast urban park in Portland, Oregon when a small mistake derails their lives forever.
A widower who realized his only connection to his family was through his wife sets off on an impromptu road trip to reunite with each of his grown children.
A young swordsman comes to Paris and faces villains, romance, adventure and intrigue with three Musketeer friends.
Nine people explore a cruise ship at sea in a manner that turns their whole lives upside down.
An American POW leads a group of mainly British prisoners to escape from the Germans in WWII.

Chronicles the motorcycle trip of Ben Tyler as he rides from Toronto to Tofino, British Columbia. Ben stops at landmarks that are both iconic and idiosyncratic on his quest to find meaning in his life.
During the Mexican Rebellion of 1866, an unsavory group of American adventurers are hired by the forces of Emporer Maximilian to escort a countess to Vera Cruz.
After a collision with a shipping container at sea, a resourceful sailor finds himself, despite all efforts to the contrary, staring his mortality in the face.
James Bond heads to the Bahamas to recover two nuclear warheads stolen by S.P.E.C.T.R.E. Agent Emilio Largo in an international extortion scheme.

A Civil War veteran agrees to deliver a girl, taken by the Kiowa people years ago, to her aunt and uncle, against her will. They travel hundreds of miles and face grave dangers as they search for a place that either can call home.
A man stranded in the Arctic after a plane crash must decide whether to remain in the relative safety of his makeshift camp or to embark on a deadly trek through the unknown.
Seven gunmen from a variety of backgrounds are brought together by a vengeful young widow to protect her town from the private army of a destructive industrialist.
A British banker hires a group of British mercenaries to rescue a deposed African President from the hands of a corrupt African dictator.

When the first manned flight to Mars is deemed unsafe and scrubbed on the launch pad, anxious authorities must scramble to save face and retain their funding - and so an unthinkable plot to fake the mission is hatched.
Marshal Rooster Cogburn unwillingly teams up with Eula Goodnight to track down her father's murderers.

Settlers traveling through the Oregon desert in 1845 find themselves stranded in harsh conditions.

A young teenager camping in the woods helps rescue the President of the United States when Air Force One is shot down near his campsite.

Navy S.E.A.L. sniper Chris Kyle's pinpoint accuracy saves countless lives on the battlefield and turns him into a legend. Back home with his family after four tours of duty, however, Chris finds that it is the war he can't leave behind.

Antwone Fisher, a young navy man, is forced to see a psychiatrist after a violent outburst against a fellow crewman. During the course of treatment a painful past is revealed and a new hope begins.

The biography of Ron Kovic. Paralyzed in the Vietnam war, he becomes an anti-war and pro-human rights political activist after feeling betrayed by the country for which he fought.

column1: Un lancer a un million de dollars
column8: A sports agent stages an unconventional recruitment strategy to get talented Indian cricket players to play Major League Baseball.
A film about the life and career of the American painter, Jackson Pollock.

The story of Christine Chubbuck, a 1970s TV reporter struggling with depression and professional frustrations as she tries to advance her career.

A family takes in an injured Magpie that makes a profound difference in their lives.

Following the assassination of President John F. Kennedy, First Lady Jacqueline Kennedy fights through grief and trauma to regain her faith, console her children, and define her husband's historic legacy.
The story of Coco Chanel's rise from obscure beginnings to the heights of the fashion world.

A young, capable professional cannot explain her newly erratic behavior.

A group of U.S. soldiers returning from Iraq struggle to integrate back into family and civilian life, while living with the memory of a war that threatens to destroy them long after they've left the battlefield.
Iranian-Canadian journalist Maziar Bahari is detained by Iranian forces who brutally interrogate him under suspicion that he is a spy.

When her 14-year-old son drowns in a lake, a faithful mother prays for him to come back from the brink of death and be healed.
The story of Linda Lovelace, who is used and abused by the porn industry at the behest of her coercive husband before taking control of her life.

Three courageous young Americans prevent a terrorist attack on a train bound for Paris.
Maverick teacher John Keating uses poetry to embolden his boarding school students to new heights of self-expression.

A boy leaves his small country town and heads to the big city to get a job. As soon as he makes it big his sweetheart will join him and marry him. His enthusiasm to get ahead leads to some interesting adventures.

column1: Monty Python : La Vie de Brian
column8: Born on the original Christmas in the stable next door to Jesus Christ, Brian of Nazareth spends his life being mistaken for a messiah.

After the death of his employer forces him out of the only home he's ever known, a simpleminded, sheltered gardener becomes an unlikely trusted advisor to a powerful tycoon and an insider in Washington politics.

An American grandson of the infamous scientist, struggling to prove that his grandfather was not as insane as people believe, is invited to Transylvania, where he discovers the process that reanimates a dead body.
A series of stories following a week in the life of a philandering tabloid journalist living in Rome.
In West Berlin during the Cold War, a Coca-Cola executive is given the task of taking care of his boss' socialite daughter.
A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

column1: A la poursuite de Ricky Baker
column8: A national manhunt is ordered for a rebellious kid and his foster uncle who go missing in the wild New Zealand bush.

In the forests of the Pacific Northwest, a father devoted to raising his six kids with a rigorous physical and intellectual education is forced to leave his paradise and enter the world, challenging his idea of what it means to be a parent.
An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

column1: La folle journee de Ferris Bueller
column8: A high school wise guy is determined to have a day off from school, despite what the Principal thinks of that.
Five high school students meet in Saturday detention and discover how they have a lot more in common than they thought.
In Berlin, an alcoholic man, recently released from prison, joins his elderly friend and a prostitute in a determined dream to leave Germany and seek a better life in Wisconsin.

Monsieur Hulot curiously wanders around a high-tech Paris, paralleling a trip with a group of American tourists. Meanwhile, a nightclub/restaurant prepares its opening night, but it's still under construction.
A couple's attitudes are challenged when their daughter introduces them to her African-American fiancé.
While trying to secure a $1 million donation for his museum, a befuddled paleontologist is pursued by a flighty and often irritating heiress and her pet leopard, Baby.

Three buddies wake up from a bachelor party in Las Vegas, with no memory of the previous night and the bachelor missing. They make their way around the city in order to find their friend before his wedding.

When the kinetic Rory moves into his room in the Carrigmore Residential Home for the Disabled, his effect on the home is immediate. Most telling is his friendship with Michael, a young man with cerebral palsy and nearly unintelligible speech. Somehow, Rory understands Michael, and encourages him to experience life outside the confines of home.
A faded movie star and a neglected young woman form an unlikely bond after crossing paths in Tokyo.
A lovelorn screenwriter becomes desperate as he tries and fails to adapt 'The Orchid Thief' by Susan Orlean for the screen.
Three company workers who hate their jobs decide to rebel against their greedy boss.

The lives of several individuals intertwine as they go about their lives in their own unique ways, engaging in acts society as a whole might find disturbing in a desperate search for human connection.
A working-class family from Melbourne, Australia fights city hall after being told they must vacate their beloved family home to allow for infrastructural expansion.
Becoming an orphan in 1935, Collin moves to his dad's cousins Verena and Dolly. Verena is a rich, bossy businesswoman. Dolly, Collin and the maid revolt, moving to a tree house.
A day in the lives of two convenience clerks named Dante and Randal as they annoy customers, discuss movies, and play hockey on the store roof.
The day-to-day lives of several suburban Los Angeles residents.
"Documentary" about a man who can look and act like whoever he's around, and meets various famous people.

column1: Y a-t-il un pilote dans l'avion?
column8: A man afraid to fly must ensure that a plane lands safely after the pilots become sick.
A study of the lives and romantic entanglements of various interconnected women.
Behind Vatican walls, the conservative Pope Benedict XVI and the liberal future Pope Francis must find common ground to forge a new path for the Catholic Church.

column1: Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood
column8: A faded television actor and his stunt double strive to achieve fame and success in the final years of Hollywood's Golden Age in 1969 Los Angeles.
Zak runs away from his care home to make his dream of becoming a wrestler come true.

"Mr. Church" tells the story of a unique friendship that develops when a little girl and her dying mother retain the services of a talented cook - Henry Joseph Church. What begins as a six month arrangement instead spans into fifteen years and creates a family bond that lasts forever.
A world-weary political journalist picks up the story of a woman's search for her son, who was taken away from her decades ago after she became pregnant and was forced to live in a convent.
Two co-dependent high school seniors are forced to deal with separation anxiety after their plan to stage a booze-soaked party goes awry.
The adventures of high school and junior high students on the last day of school in May 1976.
In 1969, two substance-abusing, unemployed actors retreat to the countryside for a holiday that proves disastrous.
A Chicago advertising man must struggle to travel home from New York for Thanksgiving, with a lovable oaf of a shower curtain ring salesman as his only companion.
A New Yorker newly separated from his wife moves in with his best friend, a divorced sportswriter, but their ideas of housekeeping and lifestyles are as different as night and day.
A Chinese family discovers their grandmother has only a short while left to live and decide to keep her in the dark, scheduling a wedding to gather before she dies.
A man who has made a new life for himself and the daughter left on his doorstep 6 years ago finds his family threatened when the birth mother resurfaces.

column1: Dans l'ombre de Mary : La Promesse de Walt Disney
column8: Author P.L. Travers reflects on her childhood after reluctantly meeting with Walt Disney, who seeks to adapt her Mary Poppins books for the big screen.

At a Montréal public grade school, an Algerian immigrant is hired to replace a popular teacher who committed suicide in her classroom. While helping his students deal with their grief, his own recent loss is revealed.

Boy, an 11-year-old child and devout Michael Jackson fan who lives on the east coast of New Zealand in 1984, gets a chance to know his absentee criminal father, who has returned to find a bag of money he buried years ago.

column10: ['Johnny Depp', 'Benicio Del Toro', 'Tobey Maguire', 'Michael Lee Gogin']

column8: This ultimate tribute to all independent filmmakers takes place during one day on the set of a non-budget movie.
A travelling theater group find so much action going on behind-the-scenes, they almost ruin the performances.

An elderly Charlie Chaplin discusses his autobiography with his editor, recounting his amazing journey from his poverty-stricken childhood to world-wide success after the ingenious invention of the Little Tramp.
The Griswold family's plans for a big family Christmas predictably turn into a big disaster.
A snobbish investor and a wily street con artist find their positions reversed as part of a bet by two callous millionaires.

column1: La premiere folie des Monty Python
column8: An anthology of the best sketches from the first and second seasons of Monty Python's Flying Circus ; Absurde, n'est-il pas? (1969).
In 2002, an artistically inclined seventeen-year-old girl comes of age in Sacramento, California.
A group of Lebanese women try to ease religious tensions between Christians and Muslims in their village.

Shy 14-year-old Duncan goes on summer vacation with his mother, her overbearing boyfriend, and her boyfriend's daughter. Having a rough time fitting in, Duncan finds an unexpected friend in Owen, manager of the Water Wizz water park.
An impoverished farmer's threat to end his life invites attention from politicians and media.
A look at four seasons in the lives of a happily married couple and their relationships with their family and friends.
Five assassins aboard a swiftly-moving bullet train to find out that their missions have something in common.
A political satire about a group of skeptical American and British operatives attempting to prevent a war between two countries.
Black Dynamite is the greatest African-American action star of the 1970s. When his only brother is killed by The Man, it's up to him to find justice.

Prison guard Vince tells Molly from acting class, that one inmate is his 24 y.o. love child. Vince takes him home to stay with his family - straight A son with fat girl fetish, college dropout/stripper daughter and cute wife.
A behind-the-scenes look into the highly competitive and cut-throat world of dog shows through the eyes of a group of ruthless dog owners.
An aspiring director and the marginally talented amateur cast of a hokey small-town Missouri musical production go overboard when they learn that someone from Broadway will be in attendance.
An awkward seventh-grader struggles to cope with inattentive parents, snobbish class-mates, a smart older brother, an attractive younger sister and her own insecurities in suburban New Jersey.
A Brooklyn smoke shop is the center of neighborhood activity, and the stories of its customers.
In WW2, an Italian Army unit of misfits occupies an isolated non-strategic Greek island for the duration of the war.
A shop assistant, her cook husband, and their twin daughters ponder their lives over a few weeks in a working-class suburb north of London.
A lonely German woman ends up in the most desolate motel on Earth and decides to make it brighter.
A nostalgic look at radio's golden age focusing on one ordinary family and the various performers in the medium.
A New Yorker's life is thrown into a tailspin when his younger cousin surprise-visits him, starting a strange, unpredictable adventure.
In his attempts to reconcile a lounge singer with his mistress, a hapless talent agent is mistaken as her lover by a jealous gangster.
Follows hard-to-please Aurora looking for love, and her daughter's family problems.
Wong Fei-Hung is a mischievous yet righteous young man, but after a series of incidents his frustrated father has him disciplined by a master of drunken martial arts.
At a 1962 college, Dean Vernon Wormer is determined to expel the entire Delta Tau Chi Fraternity, but those troublemakers have other plans for him.
A bigoted Frenchman finds himself forced to impersonate a popular rabbi while on the run from a group of assassins - and the police.
A clerical mistake results in a bumbling Indian film star being invited to an exclusive Hollywood party instead of being fired.
After being freed from his life in an underground bunker, a man sets out to make a movie of the only TV show he has ever known.
Follows Stevie, a thirteen-year-old in 1990s-era Los Angeles who spends his summer navigating between his troubled home life and a group of new friends that he meets at a Motor Avenue skate shop.
A bachelor enjoys his sweet life on the French Riviera until a one-night stand tells him, he's dad to Gloria and leaves her with him. He moves to London with Gloria. Mom turns up 8 years later.
The story of a teenage boy, his mother, and two other women who help raise him among the love and freedom of Southern California of 1979.
A practical joking father tries to reconnect with his hard working daughter by creating an outrageous alter ego and posing as her CEO's life coach.

Julián receives an unexpected visit from his friend Tomás, who lives in Canada. The two men, accompanied by Julián's faithful dog, Truman, will share emotional and surprising moments prompted by Julián's complicated situation.
When Greg Sestero, an aspiring film actor, meets the weird and mysterious Tommy Wiseau in an acting class, they form a unique friendship and travel to Hollywood to make their dreams come true.
The Kadam family leaves India for France where they open a restaurant directly across the road from Madame Mallory's Michelin-starred eatery.
A head chef quits his restaurant job and buys a food truck in an effort to reclaim his creative promise, while piecing back together his estranged family.
A man suffering a family loss enrolls in a class about care-giving that changes his perspective on life.
A New York socialite, deeply troubled and in denial, arrives in San Francisco to impose upon her sister. She looks like a million dollars but isn't bringing money, peace or love.
An aimless university dropout attempts to make sense of life as he spends one fateful day wandering the streets of Berlin.
High-school life gets even more unbearable for Nadine when her best friend, Krista, starts dating her older brother.
Chaos ensues when a man tries to expose a dark secret regarding a recently deceased patriarch of a dysfunctional British family.
After Homer pollutes the town's water supply, Springfield is encased in a gigantic dome by the EPA and the Simpsons are declared fugitives.

column8: Kazakh TV talking head Borat is dispatched to the United States to report on the greatest country in the world. With a documentary crew in tow, Borat becomes more interested in locating and marrying Pamela Anderson.
A calamity at Dante and Randal's shops sends them looking for new horizons - but they ultimately settle at the fast food empire Mooby's.
Follows two young boys dealing with their parents' divorce in Brooklyn in the 1980s.
When a lottery winner dies of shock, his fellow townsfolk attempt to claim the money.

With only the plan of moving in together after high school, two unusually devious friends seek direction in life. As a mere gag, they respond to a man's newspaper ad for a date, only to find it will greatly complicate their lives.

Suffering from writer's block and eagerly awaiting his writing award, Harry Block remembers events from his past and scenes from his best-selling books as characters, real and fictional, come back to haunt him.
After a woman leaves a briefcase at the airport terminal, a dumb limo driver and his dumber friend set out on a hilarious cross-country road trip to Aspen to return it.
The Griswold family's cross-country drive to the Walley World theme park proves to be much more arduous than they ever anticipated.

column1: Le Marin des Mers de Chine
column8: Fighting against pirates at the turn of the 20th century, the Hong Kong navy are failing miserably. It's up to Sergeant Lung (Jackie Chan) to take matters into his own hands.

column1: Les dieux sont tombes sur la tete
column8: A comic allegory about a traveling Bushman who encounters modern civilization and its stranger aspects, including a clumsy scientist and a band of revolutionaries.
A fluid, unconnected and sometimes chaotic procession of scenes detailing the various people and events of life in Italy's capital, most of it based on director Federico Fellini's life.

column8: Monsieur Hulot comes to a beachside hotel for a vacation and accidentally, but good-naturedly, causes havoc.

Eddie Murphy portrays real-life legend Rudy Ray Moore, a comedy and rap pioneer who proved naysayers wrong when his hilarious, obscene, kung-fu fighting alter ego, Dolemite, became a 1970s Blaxploitation phenomenon.

In the early 1960s, CIA agent Napoleon Solo and KGB operative Illya Kuryakin participate in a joint mission against a mysterious criminal organization, which is working to proliferate nuclear weapons.
A reporter casts a fake Bin Laden to act in his video message to America, so he can immigrate there.
Mikey Saber is a washed-up porn star who returns to his small Texas hometown, not that anyone really wants him back.

column1: Good Luck to You, Leo Grande
column8: Nancy Stokes, a retired school teacher, is yearning for some adventure, and some sex. And she has a plan, which involves hiring a young sex worker named Leo Grande.

A look at the lives of the strong-willed women of the Weston family, whose paths have diverged until a family crisis brings them back to the Oklahoma house they grew up in, and to the dysfunctional woman who raised them.
In Hamburg, German-Greek chef Zinos unknowingly disturbs the peace in his locals-only restaurant by hiring a more talented chef.
A year after their father's funeral, three brothers travel across India by train in an attempt to bond with each other.

Popular Broadway actor Gary Johnston is recruited by the elite counter-terrorism organization Team America: World Police. As the world begins to crumble around him, he must battle with terrorists, celebrities and falling in love.

An English Professor tries to deal with his wife leaving him, the arrival of his editor who has been waiting for his book for seven years, and the various problems that his friends and associates involve him in.
Arnold rescued Thomas from a fire when he was a child. Thomas thinks of Arnold as a hero, while Arnold's son Victor resents his father's alcoholism, violence and abandonment of his family.
Two young boys, both social outcasts in their small town, form an unlikely friendship.

Two business executives--one an avowed misogynist, the other recently emotionally wounded by his love interest--set out to exact revenge on the female gender by seeking out the most innocent, uncorrupted girl they can find and ruining her life.

column1: The Full Monty: Le grand jeu
column8: Six unemployed steel workers form a male striptease act. The women cheer them on to go for "the full monty" - total nudity.
A wannabe actor has a hard time moving on from a break-up, but he is lucky to have supportive friends.
A gay cabaret owner and his drag queen companion agree to put up a false straight front so that their son can introduce them to his fiancée's right-wing moralistic parents.
It's Friday, and Craig and Smokey must come up with $200 they owe a local bully or there won't be a Saturday.
A young social outcast in Australia steals money from her parents to finance a vacation where she hopes to find happiness, and perhaps love.
Bambino tries to teach his brother Trinity how to become an outlaw, but the two wind up saving a pioneer family and breaking up an arms ring instead.
In 19th century India, three British soldiers and a native waterbearer must stop a secret mass revival of the murderous Thuggee cult before it can rampage across the land.

Scott has been a case of arrested development since his firefighter dad died. He spends his days smoking weed and dreaming of being a tattoo artist until events force him to grapple with his grief and take his first steps forward in life.
An unlikely friendship between two misfit neighbors becomes an unexpectedly emotional journey when the younger man is diagnosed with terminal cancer.

On the eve of their high-school graduation, two academic superstars and best friends realize they should have worked less and played more. Determined not to fall short of their peers, the girls try to cram four years of fun into one night.
At a Jewish funeral service with her parents, a college student runs into her sugar daddy and ex girlfriend.
A sister and brother face the realities of familial responsibility as they begin to care for their ailing father.
Cady Heron is a hit with The Plastics, the A-list girl clique at her new school, until she makes the mistake of falling for Aaron Samuels, the ex-boyfriend of alpha Plastic Regina George.

column1: Presentateur vedette: La legende de Ron Burgundy
column8: Ron Burgundy is San Diego's top-rated newsman in the male-dominated broadcasting of the 1970s, but that's all about to change for Ron and his cronies when an ambitious woman is hired as a new anchor.
After his auto-parts tycoon father dies, the overweight, underachieving son teams up with a snide accountant to try and save the family business.
After a bitter divorce, an actor disguises himself as a female housekeeper to spend time with his children held in custody by his former wife.
A nerd gets himself in hot water with the new bully, a quiet bad boy who challenges him to fight on the grounds of their high school after the day's end.

column1: Qu'est-ce que j'ai fait pour meriter ca?
column8: The vicissitudes of Gloria, a neurotic housewife, and her family's peculiar characters.
A jazz musician and a stunt man are the spitting image of two millionaire brothers. They take the job to replace them in Rio de Janeiro when someone plans to assassinate them.

column1: Quand faut y aller, faut y aller
column8: Two men meet in a strange situation and end up being mistaken first for robbers, then for Secret Service agents.
A group of seven former college friends gather for a weekend reunion at a South Carolina vacation home after the funeral of another of their college friends.
A struggling young writer finds his life and work dominated by his unfaithful wife and his radical feminist mother, whose best-selling manifesto turns her into a cultural icon.
A group of Southern California high school students are enjoying their most important subjects: sex, drugs and rock n' roll.
A group of college-age buddies struggle with their imminent passage into adulthood in 1959 Baltimore.
A simpleminded, sheltered country boy suddenly decides to leave his family home to experience life in the big city, where his naivete is both his best friend and his worst enemy.
A man is trying desperately to be certified insane during World War II, so he can stop flying missions.
Wealthy rancher G.W. McLintock uses his power and influence in the territory to keep the peace between farmers, ranchers, land-grabbers, Indians and corrupt government officials.
A desk-bound CIA analyst volunteers to go undercover to infiltrate the world of a deadly arms dealer, and prevent diabolical global disaster.
To survive, a dying Newfoundland fishing village must convince a young doctor to take up residence by any means necessary.

column1: Le vieux qui ne voulait pas feter son anniversaire
column8: After living a long and colorful life, Allan Karlsson finds himself stuck in a nursing home. On his 100th birthday, he leaps out a window and begins an unexpected journey.
A comedic look at the relationship between a wealthy man with quadriplegia and an unemployed man with a criminal record who's hired to help him.

Steve Coogan has been asked by The Observer to tour the country's finest restaurants, but after his girlfriend backs out on him he must take his best friend and source of eternal aggravation, Rob Brydon.

While settling his recently deceased father's estate, a salesman discovers he has a sister whom he never knew about, leading both siblings to re-examine their perceptions about family and life choices.

A successful investment banker struggles after losing his wife in a tragic car crash. With the help of a customer service rep and her young son, he starts to rebuild, beginning with the demolition of the life he once knew.
Through a series of freak occurrences, a group of actors shooting a big-budget war movie are forced to become the soldiers they are portraying.
A Korean-American office worker and his Indian-American stoner friend embark on a quest to satisfy their desire for White Castle burgers.
Three friends attempt to recapture their glory days by opening up a fraternity near their alma mater.
Four teenage boys enter a pact to lose their virginity by prom night.
A world-class playboy and part-time secret agent from the 1960s emerges after thirty years in a cryogenic state to battle with his nemesis Dr. Evil.
A rejected hockey player puts his skills to the golf course to save his grandmother's house.
Bret Maverick, needing money for a poker tournament, faces various comic mishaps and challenges, including a charming woman thief.
Spike Lee's vibrant semi-autobiographical portrait of a school teacher, her stubborn jazz musician husband and their five kids living in Brooklyn in 1973.
A conservative folk singer turns his hand to politics, running for the US Senate. He is not above dirty tricks and smear campaigns to gain an advantage over his opponent.
A successful psychotherapist loses his mind after one of his most dependent patients, an obsessive-compulsive neurotic, tracks him down during his family vacation.
A day in the life of Austin, Texas as the camera roams from place to place and provides a brief look at the overeducated, the social misfits, the outcasts and the oddballs.
Bachelor and all-round slob Buck babysits his brother's rebellious teenage daughter and her cute younger brother and sister.

Thirty years after they served together in Vietnam, a former Navy Corpsman Larry "Doc" Shepherd re-unites with his old buddies, former Marines Sal Nealon and Reverend Richard Mueller, to bury his son, a young Marine killed in the Iraq War.
An estranged family gathers together in New York City for an event celebrating the artistic work of their father.
A hypochondriac working as an airport baggage handler is forced to confront his fears when a British teenager with a terminal illness enlists him to help her carry out her eccentric bucket list.
A suburban teenager comes of age under the destructive guidance of his best friend, an aimless college dropout.
In 1980, a group of college baseball players navigate their way through the freedoms and responsibilities of unsupervised adulthood.

A family of five heads to Granddad's big 75th-birthday party at an uncle's estate in rural Scotland. The parents are separated and hope their three kids won't mention it. The kids love, can talk with, and would do anything for Granddad.

Monty Wildhorn, an alcoholic novelist of Westerns, has lost his drive. His nephew pushes him to summer in quiet Belle Isle. He begrudgingly befriends a newly single mom and her 3 girls who help him find the inspiration to write again.
John Bennett, a man whose childhood wish of bringing his teddy bear to life came true, now must decide between keeping the relationship with the bear, Ted or his girlfriend, Lori.

column1: Hector et la recherche du bonheur
column8: A psychiatrist searches the globe to find the secret of happiness.
After 11 years, the Jackass crew is back for another crusade.
Two aimless middle-aged losers still living at home are forced against their will to become roommates when their parents marry.
A thirty-five-year-old video game tester has to move in with his grandma and her two old lady roommates.
A listless and alienated teenager decides to help his new friend win the class presidency in their small western high school, while he must deal with his bizarre family life back home.
After breaking up with his lover and boss, a smooth-talking man takes his teenaged nephew out on the town in search of sex.
A young man's peculiar upbringing renders him unable to competently cope with the struggle of growing up.

column1: The Dangerous Lives of Altar Boys
column8: A group of Catholic school friends, after being caught drawing an obscene comic book, plan a heist that will outdo their previous prank and make them local legends.
In early 1970s England, a Pakistani father finds the authority he has previously maintained challenged by his increasingly Anglicized children.
An orphaned Italian boy is raised amongst a circle of British and American women living in Mussolini's Italy before and during World War II.
The autobiographical story of Howard Stern, the radio rebel who is now also a TV personality, an author and a movie star.
A star bowler whose career was prematurely "cut off" hopes to ride a new prodigy to success and riches.

column8: A goofy detective specializing in animals goes in search of the missing mascot of the Miami Dolphins.
A small-time film promoter releases a kitschy horror film during the Cuban Missile Crisis.
Asian Hawk (Jackie Chan) and his bumbling sidekick are sent on a quest through Europe to find a mysterious treasure held by a shadowy organization of monks.

column8: Three female employees of a sexist, egotistical, lying, hypocritical bigot find a way to turn the tables on him.

When a bumbling New Yorker is dumped by his activist girlfriend, he travels to a tiny Latin American nation and becomes involved in its latest rebellion.

A young journalist, a seasoned cameraman and a discredited war correspondent embark on an unauthorized mission to find the No.1 war criminal in Bosnia. However, their extremely dangerous target decides to come after them.
Wild behavior forces a pair of energy drink reps to enroll in a Big Brother program.
When her husband unexpectedly disappears, a sharp-witted suburban wife and her daughters juggle their mom's romantic dilemmas and family dynamics.

column1: Les blancs ne savent pas sauter

column8: Six people meet in the Kalahari desert: a female NYC lawyer flying with a local zoologist/pilot in a mini-plane, a Cuban and an African soldier taking each other POW, a Boer elephant poacher, and a Bushman looking for his two children.

Three 6th grade boys ditch school and embark on an epic journey while carrying accidentally stolen drugs, being hunted by teenage girls, and trying to make their way home in time for a long-awaited party.
A college professor lives his life with reckless abandon after being diagnosed with a terminal illness.

An underachieving voice coach finds herself competing in the movie trailer voice-over profession against her arrogant father and his protégé.
Four socially troubled 18-year-olds from the south of England go on holiday to Malia.

Director Michael Winterbottom (Northam) attempts to shoot the adaptation of Laurence Sterne's essentially unfilmable novel, "The Life and Opinions of Tristram Shandy, Gentleman."
A group of misfits enter a Las Vegas dodgeball tournament in order to save their cherished local gym from the onslaught of a corporate health fitness chain.
Young employees at Shenaniganz restaurant collectively stave off boredom and adulthood with their antics.
When a small-town police station is threatened with shutting down because of too little crime, the police realize that something must be done.
The residents of a small town get over-excited when their hockey team gets chosen to host a televised event.

Four interlocking tales that take place in a fading hotel on New Year's Eve.

With a serial strangler on the loose, a bookkeeper wanders around town searching for the vigilante group intent on catching the killer.
A parody of Top Gun (1986) in which a talented but unstable fighter pilot must overcome the ghosts of his father and save a mission sabotaged by greedy weapons manufacturers.
A group of good-hearted, but incompetent misfits enter the police academy, but the instructors there are not going to put up with their pranks.
When the owner of a struggling used car lot is killed, it's up to the lot's hot-shot salesman to save the property from falling into the hands of the owner's ruthless brother and used-car rival.

column8: A film director and his strange friends struggle to produce the first major silent feature film in forty years.

column1: Tout ce que vous avez toujours voulu savoir sur le sexe... sans jamais oser le demander
column8: Seven stories are trying to answer the question: what is sex? Or maybe they are not trying.
An unhinged social media stalker moves to LA and ingratiates herself into the life of an Instagram star.

Checco was born into privilege in a small Italian town with a guaranteed job as a public servant. When a new reformist government vows to cut down on bureaucracy, Checco is forced to accept worsening conditions.
A father brings up his baby girl as a single dad after the unexpected death of his wife who died a day after their daughter's birth.
A journalist recounts her wartime coverage in Afghanistan.

A person of high intelligence struggles to make sense of the world as it relates to morality, relationships, sex, and leaving her apartment.
Two men, six meals in six different places on a road trip around Italy. Liguria, Tuscany, Rome, Amalfi and ending in Capri.
A struggling actor, father and husband finds himself at a major crossroads, which forces him to examine his life, his family and his career.

Three high-school seniors throw a birthday party to make a name for themselves. As the night progresses, things spiral out of control as word of the party spreads.
Borat returns from Kazakhstan to America and this time he reveals more about the American culture, the COVID-19 pandemic and the political elections.
Two weeks shy of his wedding, a socially awkward guy enters into a charade by hiring the owner of a company that provides best men for grooms in need.
In New York City, a husband and wife butt heads with the granddaughters of the elderly woman who lives in the apartment the couple owns.
Looking for answers to life's big questions, a stuttering boy joins his high school debate team.
An IT company hires an actor to serve as the company's president in order to help the business get sold to a cranky Icelander.
A coming of age story about a shy teenage boy trying to escape from the influence of his domineering mother. His world changes when he begins to work for a retired actress.

Number one NASCAR driver Ricky Bobby stays atop the heap thanks to a pact with his best friend and teammate, Cal Naughton, Jr. But when a French Formula One driver, makes his way up the ladder, Ricky Bobby's talent and devotion are put to the test.

column10: ['Michael Douglas', 'Evan Rachel Wood', 'Willis Burks II', 'Laura Kachergus']

column8: A Chicago weather man, separated from his wife and children, debates whether professional and personal success are mutually exclusive.

A husband-and-wife team play detective, but not in the traditional sense. Instead, the happy duo helps others solve their existential issues, the kind that keep you up at night, wondering what it all means.
Dumped by his girlfriend, a high school grad decides to embark on an overseas adventure in Europe with his friends.
A writer's young assistant becomes both pawn and catalyst in his boss's disintegrating household.
During a pro football strike, the owners hire substitute players.
A Chinese man travels to the Wild West to rescue a kidnapped Princess. After teaming up with a train robber, the unlikely duo takes on a Chinese traitor and his corrupt boss.
A nice-guy cop with Dissociative Identity Disorder must protect a woman on the run from a corrupt ex-boyfriend and his associates.
"Rambo" parody in which Topper Harley leads a rescue team into Iraq to save Iraqi war prisoners and all of their previous rescue teams.
A Chicago man and his family go camping with his obnoxious brother-in-law.
A group of young recruits go through boot camp during the Second World War in Biloxi, Mississippi. From the play by Neil Simon.

An American reporter goes to the Australian outback to meet an eccentric crocodile poacher and invites him to New York City.
At Adams College, a group of bullied outcasts and misfits resolve to fight back for their peace and self-respect.

column1: Mister Mom - Profession: pere au foyer
column8: After he's suddenly laid off, a husband switches roles with his wife. She returns to the workforce, and he becomes a stay-at-home dad, and he has to take care of three young children, a job he has no clue how to do.
A wacky inventor and his wife invite two other couples for a weekend party at a romantic summer house in the 1900s countryside.

Three go-go dancers holding a young girl hostage come across a crippled old man living with his two sons in the desert. After learning he's hiding a sum of cash around, the women start scheming on him.

This mix of a scripted buddy comedy road movie and a real hidden camera prank show follows the outrageous misadventures of two buds stuck in a rut who embark on a cross-country road trip to NYC. The storyline sets up shocking real pranks.
A filmmaker at a creative impasse seeks solace from her tumultuous past at a rural retreat, only to find that the woods summon her inner demons in intense and surprising ways.
A late night talk show host suspects that she may soon lose her long-running show.

Willowdean ('Dumplin'), the plus-size teenage daughter of a former beauty queen, signs up for her mom's Miss Teen Bluebonnet pageant as a protest that escalates when other contestants follow her footsteps, revolutionizing the pageant and their small Texas town.
86-year-old Irving Zisman takes a trip from Nebraska to North Carolina to take his 8 year-old grandson, Billy, back to his real father.
A small group of former classmates organize an elaborate, annual game of tag that requires some to travel all over the country.

Dave Skylark and his producer Aaron Rapaport run the celebrity tabloid show "Skylark Tonight". When they land an interview with a surprise fan, North Korean dictator Jong-Un Kim, they are recruited by the CIA to assassinate him.
High-strung father-to-be Peter Highman is forced to hitch a ride with aspiring actor Ethan Tremblay on a road trip in order to make it to his child's birth on time.

Two former Army Rangers are paired against their will on the road trip of a lifetime. Briggs (Channing Tatum) and Lulu (a Belgian Malinois) race down the Pacific Coast to get to a fellow soldier's funeral on time.
An actor prepping for an upcoming role meets a quirky grocery clerk, and together they hit the road to show each other their respective worlds.

column8: After being mistaken for terrorists and thrown into Guantánamo Bay, stoners Harold and Kumar escape and return to the U.S., where they proceed to flee across the country with federal agents in hot pursuit.

Maxwell Smart, a highly intellectual but bumbling spy working for the CONTROL agency, is tasked with preventing a terrorist attack from rival spy agency KAOS.

Four college buddies embark on a road trip to retrieve an illicit tape mistakenly mailed to a female friend.
At the end of his career, a clueless fashion model is brainwashed to kill the Prime Minister of Malaysia.
Two childhood friends are pro athletes of a national sport called BASEketball, a hybrid of baseball and basketball, and must deal with a greedy businessman scheming against their team.
When a desperate movie producer fails to get a major star for his bargain basement film, he decides to shoot the film secretly around him.
Two stumblebum inheritors are determined to rid their antique house of a mouse who is equally determined to stay where he is.
Two former U. S. Presidents, hated rivals, join forces to expose the current, corrupt President at the risk of their lives.
A high school senior visits college for the weekend, and stays at the wildest house on campus.
To get to know his girlfriend's son, a working-class good guy volunteers to pick him up from his prep school, only to learn that he isn't the nicest young man.
Three actors accept an invitation to a Mexican village to perform their onscreen bandit fighter roles, unaware that it is the real thing.

column1: Comment claquer un million de dollars par jour?

column1: The Personal History of David Copperfield
column8: A modern take on Charles Dickens's classic tale of a young orphan who is able to triumph over many obstacles.
A bickering gay couple must suddenly deal with the unexpected task of raising a 10-year-old boy.
Jay, Neil, Simon, and Will reunite in Australia for a holiday.
A high-school biology teacher looks to become a successful mixed martial arts fighter in an effort to raise money to prevent extracurricular activities from being axed at his cash-strapped school.

column8: A Belge-Francophobe customs officer is forced to team up with a Frenchman during the elimination of the Franco-Belge borders in the 90s.

Drea and Eleanor agree to go after one another's bullies.
A seemingly perfect family moves into a suburban neighborhood, but when it comes to the truth as to why they're living there, they don't exactly come clean with their neighbors.
The owner of a Miami restaurant indebted to the mob institutes a contest to see what waiter can earn the most money in one night.
It's 1987 and Danielle, the high-school 'Dirty Girl', is running away. With her is chubby, gay Clarke, a bag of flour called Joa and a Walkman full of glorious '80s tunes.

Henry Poole moves in to a house in his old neighborhood, to spend what he believes are his remaining days alone. The discovery of a "miracle" by a nosy neighbor ruptures his solitude and restores his faith in life.
A sex-addicted con-man pays for his mother's hospital bills by playing on the sympathies of those who rescue him from choking to death.

Two bumbling store clerks inadvertently erase the footage from all of the tapes in their video rental store. In order to keep the business running, they re-shoot every film in the store with their own camera, with a budget of zero dollars.
A young man, much to the chagrin of his father, becomes the new assistant to an illusionist in decline.

A high school slacker who's rejected by every school he applies to opts to create his own institution of higher learning, the South Harmon Institute of Technology, on a rundown piece of property near his hometown.
Jim and his friends are now in college, and they decide to meet up at the beach house for some fun.
A Las Vegas casino magnate, determined to find a new avenue for wagering, sets up a race for money.
Oscar and Felix take a road trip to their son and daughter's wedding.
A loser finds success in the revenge-for-hire business.
Zookeepers struggle to deal with the policies of changing directors.
Reunited by the death of a college friend, three divorced women seek revenge on the husbands who left them for younger women.

Robin shares a ride in her car with Jane from New York to Los Angeles. They stop at Jane's friend Holly's place in Pittsburgh and take her with them west, making a long stop in Tucson. The three very different women become close friends.
Two couples of sisters from New York and from the countryside discover that they are connected in an incredible way.
A young couple struggles to repair a hopelessly dilapidated house.
Two bumbling government employees think they are U.S. spies, only to discover that they are actually decoys for Nuclear War.
A series of short, highly irreverent, and often tasteless skits.

A Democratic strategist helps a retired veteran run for mayor in a small, conservative Midwest town.
A hardened CIA operative finds himself at the mercy of a precocious 9-year-old girl, having been sent undercover to surveil her family.

An uptight couple makes friends with a rowdy couple while on vacation in Mexico, but their friendship takes an awkward turn when they get back home.
Newlywed couple Ted and Tami-Lynn want to have a baby, but in order to qualify to be a parent, Ted will have to prove he's a person in a court of law.

Two salesmen whose careers have been torpedoed by the digital age find their way into a coveted internship at Google, where they must compete with a group of young, tech-savvy geniuses for a shot at employment.
After they are forced to live next to a fraternity house, a couple with a newborn baby do whatever they can to take them down.
Johnny English goes up against international assassins hunting down Chinese Premier Xiang Ping.

Tim Lippe has no idea what he's in for when he's sent to Cedar Rapids, Iowa to represent his company at an annual insurance convention, where he soon finds himself under the "guidance" of three convention veterans.

column8: With the 1970s behind them, San Diego's top-rated newsman, Ron Burgundy, returns to take New York City's first twenty-four-hour news channel by storm.

When seasoned comedian George Simmons learns of his terminal, inoperable health condition, his desire to form a genuine friendship causes him to take a relatively green performer under his wing as his opening act.

After spending two decades in England, Bill Bryson (Robert Redford) returns to the U.S., where he decides the best way to connect with his homeland is to hike the Appalachian Trail with one of his oldest friends, Stephen Katz (Nick Nolte).
A young woman gets mixed up with a disgraced spy who is trying to clear his name.
Three actors learn that their respective performances in the film "Home for Purim," a drama set in the mid-1940s American South, are generating award-season buzz.
An examination of the health risks involved in the fast food industry as well as its environmental and social consequences.
Four people meet on New Year's Eve, and form a surrogate family to help one another with the difficulties of their lives.

In 2002, two rival Olympic ice skaters were stripped of their gold medals and permanently banned from men's single competition. Presently, however, they've found a loophole that will allow them to qualify as a pairs team.

After a run-in with the law, Haley Graham (Missy Peregrym) is forced to return to the world from which she fled some years ago. Enrolled in an elite gymnastics program run by the legendary Burt Vickerman (Jeff Bridges), Haley's rebellious attitude gives way to something that just might be called team spirit.

Two dim-witted, inseparable friends hit the road for their ten-year high school reunion and concoct an elaborate lie about their lives in order to impress their classmates.
In order to inherit his fed up father's hotel empire, an immature and lazy man must repeat grades 1-12 all over again.
Rich, old uncle Joe is surrounded by relatives waiting/hoping for him to die while trying to look good and backstabbing the competition. What should he do?
Five siblings are left alone all summer when their mom leaves town and the evil babysitter bites the dust.
A teen decides to go for a night on the town with his friends despite flunking his driver's test.

column1: Gung Ho - Du sake dans le moteur
column8: When a Japanese car company buys an American plant, the American liaison must mediate the clash of work attitudes between the foreign management and native labor.
A soon-to-be-married man's friends throw him the ultimate bachelor party.

The San Fernando Valley adventures of trucker turned prize-fighter Philo Beddoe and his pet orangutan Clyde.
After a cyber-attack reveals the identity of all of the active undercover agents in Britain, Johnny English is forced to come out of retirement to find the mastermind hacker.

When four lifelong friends travel to New Orleans for the annual Essence Festival, sisterhoods are rekindled, wild sides are rediscovered, and there's enough dancing, drinking, brawling and romancing to make the Big Easy blush.
In Iowa, a girl in foster care discovers her talent for butter carving and finds herself pitted against an ambitious local woman in their town's annual contest.

column8: Six years after their Guantanamo Bay adventure, stoner buds Harold Lee and Kumar Patel cause a holiday fracas by inadvertently burning down Harold's father-in-law's prize Christmas tree.

A reporter in Iraq might just have the story of a lifetime when he meets Lyn Cassady, a guy who claims to be a former member of the U.S. Army's New Earth Army, a unit that employs paranormal powers in their missions.
Two bird enthusiasts try to defeat the cocky, cutthroat world record holder in a year-long bird-spotting competition.
A guy fed up with his job and married to a cheating wife reluctantly mentors a rebellious teen.
An inept tae kwon do instructor struggles with marital troubles and an unhealthy obsession with fellow tae kwon do enthusiast Chuck "The Truck" Wallace.
Two brothers travel to Germany for Oktoberfest, only to stumble upon a secret, centuries-old competition described as a "Fight Club" with beer games.
Satirical interpretations of world events and curious human behavior.

When a Chinese rebel murders Chon's estranged father and escapes to England, Chon and Roy make their way to London with revenge on their minds.

column8: After a sudden attack on MI5, Johnny English, Britain's most confident, yet unintelligent spy, becomes Britain's only spy.
A snowboarder's plans for his own snowboard park go awry when an ex-girlfriend returns to town.
A rough-around-the-edges martial arts master seeks revenge for his parents' death.
A year after disposing of the body of a man they accidentally killed, a group of dumb teenagers are stalked by a bumbling serial killer.

A gubernatorial candidate hires a wormy special assistant whose only job is to make sure the candidate's well-meaning but incompetent brother doesn't ruin the election.
A reformed bank robber is taken hostage by a desperate man during a bank hold up, but is forced to go on the run with his captor when they're both mistakenly thought to be in cahoots.

column8: A couple swap city life for the country, but their picturesque new hometown turns out to be just a little bit different to what they were expecting.
A rich but troubled family find their lives altered by the arrival of a vagrant who tries to drown himself in their swimming pool.
An overworked air-traffic controller takes his family on a beach vacation but is soon beset by series of mishaps.
The Griswolds win a vacation tour across Europe where the usual havoc ensues.

In 1954, a group of Florida high-school guys try to help their buddy lose his virginity, which leads them to seek revenge on a sleazy nightclub owner and his redneck sheriff brother for harassing them.

A wide variety of eccentric competitors participate in a wild and illegal cross-country road race. However, the eccentric entrants will do anything to win the road race, including low-down, dirty tricks.
A sheltered young high-society woman joins the United States Army on a whim and finds herself in a trickier situation than she ever expected.

column1: Arrete de ramer, t'es sur le sable
column8: Wacky hijinks of counselors and campers at a less-than-average summer camp.
A hypocritical swinging college student cat raises hell in a satiric vision of various elements on the 1960s.
Zach Galifianakis and his oddball crew take a road trip to complete a series of high-profile celebrity interviews.
After an innocent AOL chat turns racy, a Catholic teenager in the early 2000s discovers masturbation and struggles to suppress her new urges in the face of eternal damnation.
After she's left at the altar, a workaholic advertising executive ends up on her Caribbean honeymoon cruise with her estranged father.

A foul-mouthed former gymnastics bronze medalist with local celebrity status reluctantly trains a rising Olympics aspirant.

An incumbent Representative embroiled in personal scandal faces a no-holds-barred challenge from a naive newcomer funded by two unscrupulous billionaire lobbyist brothers.
Rusty Griswold takes his own family on a road trip to "Walley World" in order to spice things up with his wife and reconnect with his sons.
The two most popular guys in high school decide to ditch football camp for cheerleader camp. For the girls and for the glory.

A weak con man panics when he learns he's going to prison for fraud. He hires a mysterious martial arts guru who helps transform him into a martial arts expert who can fight off inmates who want to hurt or love him.

Young Augusten Burroughs absorbs experiences that could make for a shocking memoir: the son of an alcoholic father and an unstable mother, he's handed off to his mother's therapist, Dr. Finch, and spends his adolescent years as a member of Finch's bizarre extended family.
American journalist Paul Kemp takes on a freelance job in Puerto Rico for a local newspaper during the 1960s and struggles to find a balance between island culture and the expatriates who live there.
A streetwise man flees South Central Los Angeles, heading to the suburbs and his lottery-winner uncle and cousin, to avoid a neighborhood thug with a grudge who has just escaped from prison.
A big-city newspaper columnist is forced to enter a drug and alcohol rehab center after ruining her sister's wedding and crashing a stolen limousine.
A video store clerk agrees to have his life filmed by a camera crew for a television show.
Naive young Mormon Joe Young is recruited to act in porn movies.

column8: A waterboy for a college football team discovers he has a unique tackling ability and becomes a member of the team.
Lt. Cmdr. Tom Dodge is assigned as Captain to the USS Stingray, an old diesel driven submarine that has seen better days.
The original 70s TV family is now placed in the 1990s, where they're even more square and out of place than ever.
Due to NCAA sanctions, the Texas State University Fightin' Armadillos must form a football team from their actual student body, with no scholarships to help, to play their football schedule.
A trucker turned prize fighter, his brother and their pet orangutan have a series of misadventures involving the mob, corrupt cops, motorcycle gangs and pretty dames.
A playboy who refuses to give up his hedonistic lifestyle to settle down and marry his true love seeks help from a demented psychoanalyst who is having romantic problems of his own.
Best friends Audrey and Morgan unwittingly become entangled in an international conspiracy when one of them discovers that the boyfriend who dumped her was actually a spy.
Having finally gotten used to each other's existence, Brad and Dusty must now deal with their intrusive fathers during the holidays.

A reporter's dream of becoming a news anchor is compromised after a one-night stand leaves her stranded in downtown L.A. without a phone, car, ID or money - and only 8 hours to make it to the most important job interview of her life.
Former college frenemies Lauren and Katie move into a fabulous Gramercy Park apartment, and in order to make ends meet, the unlikely pair start a phone sex line together.
Two sisters decide to throw one last house party before their parents sell their family home.

Margot and her son Claude decide to visit her sister Pauline after she announces that she is marrying less-than-impressive Malcolm.

Master explorer Dirk Pitt goes on the adventure of a lifetime of seeking out a lost Civil War battleship known as the "Ship of Death" in the deserts of West Africa while helping a WHO doctor being hounded by a ruthless dictator.

Two college roommates go out and party, resulting in bad grades. They learn of the clause that says, "If your roommate dies, you get an A," and decide to find someone who is on the verge, so to speak, to move in with them.

A rookie high school football coach has a harder time than she expected trying to whip her tough inner city team into shape.
A radio journalist and his technician get in over their heads when they hatch a scheme to fake their own kidnapping during a rebel uprising in South America and hide out in New York instead.

column1: Un prof pas comme les autres 2

A suburban couple becomes embroiled in an international espionage plot when they discover that their seemingly perfect new neighbors are government spies.
Right before his wedding, an uptight guy is tricked into driving his grandfather, a lecherous former Army Lieutenant Colonel, to Florida for Spring Break.
After their high school basketball coach passes away, five good friends and former teammates reunite for a Fourth of July holiday weekend.
Flamboyant and gay Austrian Brüno looks for new fame in America.
A troubled young woman is sent to live with her grandmother for the summer, while hiding a secret that could potentially tear her family apart.
A veteran Vegas magician tries to revive his career after his longtime partner quits, he gets fired from his casino act, and an edgy new "street magician" steals his thunder.
A young guy short on luck enrolls in a class to build confidence to help win over the girl of his dreams, which becomes complicated when it turns out his teacher has the same agenda.

Four skaters follow their idol on his summer tour in an attempt to get noticed, get sponsored, and become stars themselves.
When "The Man" tries to derail a black candidate's presidential campaign, Undercover Brother and his fellow secret agents come to the rescue.
A young couple has a chance to move into a gorgeous duplex in the perfect New York neighborhood. All they have to do is bump off the current tenant, a cute little old lady.
After being abandoned by his parents at the Grand Canyon, Joe Dirt tells the story of his journey to find his parents.

After a single, career-minded woman is left on her own to give birth to the child of a married man, she finds a new romantic chance in a cab driver. Meanwhile, the point-of-view of the newborn baby is narrated through voice-over.
An anti-ageist comedy about a man's dream to win the Rucker Classic street ball tournament in Harlem.
A hockey player plagued by injuries is confronted with the possibility of retirement when a tough new player challenges his status as the league's top enforcer.
A lonely, neurotic, and hilariously honest middle-aged man reunites with his estranged wife, and meets his teenage daughter for the first time.

The night before his big medical school interview, a promising student celebrates his 21st birthday with his two best friends.
As inventor Andy Brewster is about to embark on the road trip of a lifetime, a quick stop at his mom's house turns into an unexpected cross-country voyage with her along for the ride.
Jackie Moon, the owner-coach-player of the American Basketball Association's Flint Michigan Tropics, rallies his teammates to make their NBA dreams come true.
A group of suburban biker wannabes looking for adventure hit the open road, but get more than they bargained for when they encounter a New Mexico gang called the Del Fuegos.
A grizzled little league coach tries to turn his team of misfits into champs.

A young guy's only option to erase a really bad debt is to rig the Special Olympics by posing as a contestant.
A high school senior branded uncool in the ninth grade gets himself expelled so he changes his image to cool kid at the town's other high school.

column1: Les Sexton se mettent au vert
column8: An unhappily married Manhattan socialite couple flee from the I.R.S. and end up in Amish country where they pretend to be visiting relatives.

column1: Les nouvelles aventures de la famille Brady
column8: The Bradys are surprised when a man claiming to be Carol's long lost first husband shows up at their home. Before long, his strange actions cause them to question his motives.

Sgt. Bilko is a well-liked conman in charge of the army base's motor pool, developing a hover tank and unofficially of gambling etc. One man hates Bilko and he's coming to inspect the base for possible closure.
When they find a frozen caveman in their back yard, two high school outcasts thaw him and introduce him to modern life while he in turn gets them to actually enjoy life.
A Chicagoan inherits an old yacht. He, his wife, daughter and son fly to a Caribbean island and hire a dubious Captain Ron to sail them on an adventure to Miami.
A young pilot finds himself recruited unwittingly into a covert and corrupt CIA airlift operation in Laos during the Vietnam conflict.

An underemployed reporter finds himself literally purchased as a toy for a rich spoiled brat.
Hysterical Californians prepare for a Japanese invasion in the days after Pearl Harbor.

When their new next-door neighbors turn out to be a sorority even more debaucherous than the fraternity previously living there, Mac and Kelly team with their former enemy, Teddy, to bring the girls down.

column8: When the Dean of Blue Mountain State threatens to sell the Goat House, Alex throws Thad the party of his dreams in an effort to get him to buy it.
Rachel tries to spice up her marriage with a trip to a strip club. She befriends McKenna who gave her a lapdance. She moves in with Rachel's family and becomes a nanny for the son.
A divorced couple scheme to recover the retirement money that was stolen from them.
An English teacher's life is disrupted when a former student returns to her small town after failing as a playwright in New York.
A failed New York playwright awkwardly navigates the transition from Next Big Thing to Last Year's News.
Two very different families converge on Martha's Vineyard one weekend for a wedding.
A funeral ceremony turns into a debacle of exposed family secrets and misplaced bodies.
A perpetually angry man is informed he has 90 minutes to live and promptly sets out to reconcile with his family and friends in the short time he has left.

column8: Used-car liquidator Don Ready is hired by a flailing auto dealership to turn their Fourth of July sale into a majorly profitable event.
After a young actress unknowingly eats her roommate's marijuana cupcakes, her day becomes a series of misadventures.
The owner of an historic South Side Chicago barbershop is pressured to sell out to a land developer, but must face the impact this would have on his close-knit community.
Working as security guards, Craig and Day-Day run into the thief who stole their Christmas presents.
Lavinia and Suzette, former rock groupies and best friends, reconnect after twenty years; one is still as wild as ever, while the other has adopted a more conservative lifestyle.
A sendup of all the teen movies that have accumulated in the past two decades.
With his career on the skids, a Hollywood screenwriter enlists the aid of a modern-day muse, who proves to test his patience.
Two bumbling explorers hope to beat Lewis & Clarke to the Pacific Ocean as they race across America's western frontier in the early 1800's.

Australian outback expert protects his New York love from gangsters who've followed her down under.
When a new gang moves into town it's up to the screwball police team to stop them.

As their own mothers drop in unexpectedly, our three under-appreciated and over-burdened moms rebel against the challenges and expectations of the Super Bowl for mothers: Christmas.
After her husband abruptly asks for a divorce, a middle-aged mother returns to college in order to complete her degree.
When one school teacher unwittingly causes another teacher's dismissal, he is challenged to an after-school fight.
20 years since their first adventure, Lloyd and Harry go on a road trip to find Harry's newly discovered daughter, who was given up for adoption.
Former special operative MacGruber is called back into action to take down his arch-enemy, Dieter Von Cunth, who's in possession of a nuclear warhead and bent on destroying Washington, D.C.

A grown man caught in the crossfire of his parents' 15-year divorce discovers he was unknowingly part of a study on divorced children and is enlisted in a follow-up years later, which wreaks new havoc on his family.
An Israeli Special Forces Soldier fakes his death so he can re-emerge in New York City as a hair stylist.
Two assistant managers of a corporate grocery store vie for a coveted promotion.

column8: Two weeks in the life of a fading Hollywood producer who's having a rough time trying to get his new picture made.
A determined hairstylist (Queen Latifah) competes with her former boss (Kevin Bacon) after opening her own business in Atlanta.
When a lonely guy meets a woman on the internet who happens to be in prison, she breaks out to get him to prove her innocence, and proceeds to wreak havoc on his middle-class life.
The Indians are now a World Series contender. But last year's hunger is now replaced with complacency, and bad decisions by the new owner threaten to tear the team apart.
One year after their first adventure, Mitch Robbins and his friends discover a treasure map that belonged to their late trail guide Curly and they set out to discover its secrets.
A surprisingly resourceful housewife vows revenge on her husband when he begins an affair with a wealthy romance novelist.
A rebellious stoner named Moondog lives life by his own rules.
A cheerleading stunt gone wrong landed her in a 20-year coma. Now she's 37, newly awake and ready to live out her high school dream: becoming prom queen.
Upon learning that their mother has been lying to them for years about their allegedly deceased father, two fraternal twin brothers hit the road in order to find him.
Scheming to save their father's ranch, the Alvarez brothers find themselves in a war with Mexico's most feared drug lord.

While in his teens, Donny fathered a son, Todd, and raised him as a single parent until Todd's 18th birthday. Now Donny resurfaces just before Todd's wedding after years apart, sending the groom-to-be's world crashing down.

A comedy centered around four couples who settle into a tropical-island resort for a vacation. While one of the couples is there to work on the marriage, the others fail to realize that participation in the resort's therapy sessions is not optional.
After Playboy bunny Shelley is kicked out of the playboy mansion, she finds a job as the house mother for a sorority full of socially awkward girls.
A trio of guys try and make up for missed opportunities in childhood by forming a three-player baseball team to compete against standard children's Little League squads.
A thirty-something former child star hires a foster family to re-create the childhood he never had.
Cindy must investigate mysterious crop circles and video tapes, and help the President in preventing an alien invasion.
The remake of the 1970 Neil Simon comedy follows the adventures of married couple Henry and Nancy Clark as they are vexed by misfortune while in New York City for a job interview.
A man tries to rescue a woman with a little help from his half brother.

The boxing champ's promoter thinks, change is needed. He finds the one man who's beaten his black champ (at 17), a white man now in a rock band. Like Rocky, he trains heavily whereas the champ slacks.
Three friends are on the verge of getting their video game financed when their benefactor is taken hostage by terrorists.
